<section class="walkin-tip">
  <h3>How to ask</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Go to the building's <strong>juristic office</strong> (condo) or <strong>front desk</strong> (apartment), ideally on a weekday daytime.</li>
    <li>Ask: <em>"มีห้องว่างให้เช่าไหมครับ/คะ 2 ห้องนอน?"</em> — any 2-bedroom vacant to rent? They often know owner units not listed online.</li>
    <li>Ask for the owner's contact, the monthly rent, deposit (usually 2 months + 1), and whether pets/contract length are flexible.</li>
    <li>Bigger condos (Hillside, Chom Doi, Escent) turn over constantly — worth a visit even if nothing shows online today.</li>
  </ul>
</section>
